# Configuration and Parameters

## Module Parameters
- Define parameters in proto files
- Use governance for parameter changes
- Validate parameters on update in `Validate()` method: check ranges, relationships
- Return clear error messages

## Configuration Files
- Use TOML for configuration files
- Node: `~/.volnix/config/config.toml`, App: `~/.volnix/config/app.toml`
- Organize by component, document all options, provide defaults

## Environment Variables
- Use for sensitive data and deployment-specific configs
- Naming: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE, prefix with module name when appropriate
- Example: `VOLNIX_NODE_RPC_ADDRESS=localhost:26657`
- Document in README

## Genesis Configuration
- Define in `genesis.proto`
- Validate all genesis parameters, check parameter relationships
- Verify initial state

## Best Practices
- Keep configuration simple, use sensible defaults
- Validate on load, support hot-reload where possible
- Don't commit sensitive data, use environment variables for secrets
- Restrict configuration file permissions
